  "description": "<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<p>An interesting narrow slot to visit on the way to/from Las Vegas.\nThere are also couple small caves in the vicinity that may be worth a\nvisit.</p>\n<h2 id=\"approach\">Approach</h2>\n<p>If exiting interstate 15 at Afton, you will need to cross the Mojave\nRiver. It could potentially be too high for a passenger vehicle. If\ntaking the Basin Rd exit be prepared ot off road a little bit with some\nsoft sand.</p>\n<h2 id=\"descent\">Descent</h2>\n<p>The canyon is approached from the bottom by ascending the canyon\nitself. First you go up canyon climbing the drops with partner assists\nand occasionally some static ropes. Then you come back down with the\noption to rappel or just handline it.</p>\n<p>Make sure you pack a headlamp. The canyon gets so narrow and the\nwalls so high that you will be plunged in complete darkness.</p>\n<h2 id=\"exit\">Exit</h2>\n<p>The topology of this area has changed considerably since the USGS\nTopo was created, double check a recent map or image source if you plan\nto exit the canyon any way other than back down it.</p>\n<h2 id=\"red_tape\">Red tape</h2>\n<h2 id=\"beta_sites\">Beta sites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://brennen.caltech.edu/swhikes/aftonc.htm\">Chris Brennen's\nAdventure Hikes (Southwest)</a> : Afton Canyon Slot</li>\n<li><img src=\"rwl_en.png\" title=\"rwl_en.png\" alt=\"rwl_en.png\" /><a\nhref=\"http://summitpost.org/afton-canyon/881046\">SummitPost.org</a> :\nAfton Canyon</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media</h2>\n<h2 id=\"background\">Background</h2>\n",
